Thank you so much for serving your community by volunteering at the tool library\!

### Before arriving

If you don't already have an account, [create one on our inventory management system MyTurn](https://capitolhill.myturn.com/library/createUser/create). The MyTurn signup process also includes signing our liability waiver.

### Attire

Wear close-toed shoes, and avoid dangling clothing, hair, or accessories. You'll be working near heavy objects and power tools, so helps to be careful\!

### Location

We're at [1552 Crawford Pl, Seattle, WA 98122](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Capitol+Hill+Tool+Library/@47.6146948,-122.3287445,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x54906acb3c54ed9d:0x3aeb6dec453e9992!8m2!3d47.6146912!4d-122.3261642!16s%2Fg%2F11cky79hb4?entry=ttu), halfway down the Crawford Place alleyway between Pike and Pine in Capitol Hill. If you have trouble finding us day-of, you can call the library phone at 206-420-7005.

### Transportation

The closest bus routes are the [10](https://kingcounty.gov/en/dept/metro/routes-and-service/schedules-and-maps/010/#route-map), [11](https://kingcounty.gov/en/dept/metro/routes-and-service/schedules-and-maps/011/#route-map), and [49](https://kingcounty.gov/en/dept/metro/routes-and-service/schedules-and-maps/049/#route-map). If you bike in, you can store your bike safely inside during your shift. If you need to drive, Capitol Hill has free street parking on Sundays but otherwise you'll need to park several blocks away to avoid [expensive parking meters](https://seattlecitygis.maps.arcgis.com/apps/MapSeries/index.html?appid=5fc6cb313ec34374a3141d4d24b05c5d).

### Expectations

Shift volunteers are expected to be present for as much of the shift as possible, and are expected to serve patrons or work on tool library initiatives rather than work on their own personal projects.
